    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-07T06:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-07T06:44:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-07T11:00:00-00:44"
                            >September 7, 1929—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Referring to Department’s No. 33, August 28, 8 p.m. Officially informed terms
                    of reference completed in the form of our discussions. Not to be published at
                    this time. Request from Liberia yesterday Government of the United States
                    recommend member of the Commission. Request to League made direct. See my 46,
                    follows.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
